### ============================================================
### Fake-Fiori-Server – Draft-Support Tests
### Server: http://localhost:8000
### ============================================================

### 1. Metadata prüfen – DraftRoot, IsActiveEntity, DraftAdministrativeData
GET http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/$metadata HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/xml

### 2. Products abrufen – Draft-Properties (IsActiveEntity, HasActiveEntity, HasDraftEntity)
GET http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products?$top=1 HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### 3. Composite Key Lookup – Products(ProductID='P001',IsActiveEntity=true)
GET http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products(ProductID='P001',IsActiveEntity=true) HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### 4. Boolean-Filter – $filter=IsActiveEntity eq true
GET http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products?$filter=IsActiveEntity%20eq%20true&$top=2 HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### 5. draftEdit – Draft-Kopie erstellen (IsActiveEntity wird false)
POST http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products(ProductID='P001',IsActiveEntity=true)/Service.draftEdit HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{"PreserveChanges": true}

### 6. PATCH auf Draft – Feld im Draft ändern
PATCH http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products(ProductID='P001',IsActiveEntity=false) HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{"ProductName": "Laptop Pro 15 (geändert)"}

### 7. draftPrepare – Validierung (No-Op, gibt Draft zurück)
POST http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products(ProductID='P001',IsActiveEntity=false)/Service.draftPrepare HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{"SideEffectsQualifier": ""}

### 8. draftActivate – Draft aktivieren (Änderungen in aktives Entity übernehmen)
POST http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products(ProductID='P001',IsActiveEntity=false)/Service.draftActivate HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{}

### 9. Prüfen dass P001 wieder aktiv ist und kein Draft existiert
GET http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products(ProductID='P001',IsActiveEntity=true) HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### 10. Zweites Entity testen – Draft für P002 erstellen
POST http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products(ProductID='P002',IsActiveEntity=true)/Service.draftEdit HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{"PreserveChanges": true}

### 11. Draft von P002 patchen
PATCH http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products(ProductID='P002',IsActiveEntity=false) HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{"ProductName": "Updated Name"}

### 12. Draft von P002 aktivieren
POST http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products(ProductID='P002',IsActiveEntity=false)/Service.draftActivate HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{}

### 13. Service Document
GET http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/ HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### 14. Collection mit $count
GET http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products/$count HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### 15. Simple Key Lookup (altes Format)
GET http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products('P001') HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### 16. Orders – Draft-Unterstützung prüfen
GET http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Orders?$top=1 HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### 17. Orders – draftEdit
POST http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Orders(OrderID='O001',IsActiveEntity=true)/Service.draftEdit HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{"PreserveChanges": true}

### 18. Orders – Draft patchen
PATCH http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Orders(OrderID='O001',IsActiveEntity=false) HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{"CustomerName": "Neuer Kunde GmbH"}

### 19. Orders – draftActivate
POST http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Orders(OrderID='O001',IsActiveEntity=false)/Service.draftActivate HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{}

### ============================================================
### Draft Discard (Verwerfen) – DELETE
### ============================================================

### 20. Draft erstellen für P003
POST http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products(ProductID='P003',IsActiveEntity=true)/Service.draftEdit HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{"PreserveChanges": true}

### 21. Prüfen: Aktives Entity hat HasDraftEntity=true
GET http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products(ProductID='P003',IsActiveEntity=true) HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### 22. Draft verwerfen (DELETE) – gibt 204 No Content zurück
DELETE http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products(ProductID='P003',IsActiveEntity=false) HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### 23. Prüfen: Aktives Entity hat HasDraftEntity=false, Daten unverändert
GET http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Products(ProductID='P003',IsActiveEntity=true) HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### 24. Orders – Draft erstellen und verwerfen
POST http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Orders(OrderID='O002',IsActiveEntity=true)/Service.draftEdit HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{"PreserveChanges": true}

### 25. Orders – Draft patchen
PATCH http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Orders(OrderID='O002',IsActiveEntity=false) HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{"CustomerName": "Wird verworfen GmbH"}

### 26. Orders – Draft verwerfen (DELETE)
DELETE http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Orders(OrderID='O002',IsActiveEntity=false) HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### 27. Orders – Prüfen dass aktives Entity unverändert ist
GET http://localhost:8000/odata/v4/Service/Orders(OrderID='O002',IsActiveEntity=true) HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
